<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="intend-vt">intend <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪn'tend/    美 /ɪn'tend/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>打算；想要：</strong></h4>
<p>to plan or mean to do sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I intend no harm. 
我没有恶意。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>intend doing / to do sth：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He intends studying / to study abroad next year.
他打算明年去国外学习。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>intend sb / sth to do sth：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I intend you to come with me. 
我想让你跟我一起去。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>intend + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We intend that / It <strong>is intended that</strong> production will start next month.
我们打算下个月开始生产。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>intended /ɪn'tendɪd/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The book is <strong>intended for</strong> children.
这书是给孩子们读的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His visit <strong>is intended to</strong> strengthen ties between the two countries.
他此次访问旨在增进两国间的关系。</p></div></div>